external_knowledge:
- 'spring' refers to the second quarter (Q2);
- 'before the turn of the millennium' means before the year 2000;
- 'most lucrative' means the movies that generated the highest revenue.

- "cinematic gems" refers to movies;
- "golden flowers" symbolizes highly profitable movies;
- Profit percentage formula: ((Revenue - Adjusted Budget) / Adjusted Budget) * 100;
- "planted with" is a metaphor for the initial investment into a movie.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM release_years 
WHERE release_year = 2015 AND release_quarter = 'Q3';

SELECT AVG(runtime) AS average_runtime
FROM movies
WHERE LENGTH(spoken_languages) - LENGTH(REPLACE(spoken_languages, ',', '')) > 0;

SELECT m.original_title, ry.release_year 
FROM movies m 
INNER JOIN release_years ry ON m.movie_id = ry.movie_id;

